Former Gatanga MP Peter Kenneth has emerged as the most preferred running mate for Azimio-One Kenya Alliance presidential aspirant Raila Odinga. In a poll conducted by Radio Africa Group, Kenneth was the most preferred person with 31.0 per cent support. Former vice president Kalonzo Musyoka came in second at 26.0 per cent, while Martha Karua closed the top three in the list of the most preferred running mates at 24.0 per cent. The poll was conducted between April 1 and 13, 2022, with 4,497 respondents from all 47 counties weighted to reflect the IEBC register for November 2021.